                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.61331/170: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-17T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 17, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>359. Tsingtao’s 212, November 13, 11 a.m., and your despatch 4170 of October
                        9,<note n="21" xml:id="d467fn21">Latter not printed.</note> Universal Leaf
                    Tobacco Company. The head office of the company in this country has informed the
                    Department that the proposal outlined in Tsingtao’s telegram under reference is
                    contrary to its best business judgment and that it has cabled its Shanghai
                    office “recommending that they do not agree because the proposal is not only
                    unreasonable but in our opinion involves illegal restrictions”.</p>
                <p>In view of the flagrant nature of this instance of Japanese interference with
                    American business in China, the Department desires that unless you perceive
                    objection you make a further approach to the Foreign Office in regard to the
                    case and that Tsingtao continue to press appropriate Japanese authorities at
                    that port.</p>
                <p>Sent to Tokyo via Shanghai. Repeated to Tsingtao.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
